rComments: I have to admit, I was looking forward to 20th Century European history. And Dr. Carter-Chand certainly was very monotone and dry in her lectures, which did kill a bit of enthusiasm but not by much.

Professor Carter-Chand was one of the WORST professors I have ever had!  She is incredible boring with the way she delivers lectures: her monotone voice destroys my enthusiasm;  puts me to sleep no matter how exciting the topic is, and she is unprepared for lectures (technical difficulties all the time), tests poorly structured

One of the most boring, monotone professors I've ever had.  Her lecture slides are unhelpful, her midterm and exam were formatted terribly, and she is overall a very poor prof.  Can do well if you read the textbook and don't attend lecture.  Should have been an interesting class (modern European history) but avoid if she teaches it.
Not very passionate and always reads off notes. Seems to be relatively unprepared when going through slides as well. Great syllabus, but the course is let down by the prof.
very bad at lecturing. always reading off notes and will brush by important points with very little clarification. unorganized. if youre taking an unfamiliar subject w her i wouldnt recommend at all
